\begin{align*}
s_1 &= (-4+r(r-3))+r \\
    &= -4+r^2-2r \hspace{1cm}\text{using }r(s-3)=r=\displaystyle \frac{n(r-3)}{r^2}=-\frac{4}{r} \\
    &= \frac{-1-r}4.
\end{align*}
It is easy to check that $s_1$ is a root of $x^2+x+1$.  By Vieta's formulas we have $\displaystyle s_1s_2=\frac{m}1=1$, so $\displaystyle s_2=s_1^{-1} = \frac{1}{s_1} = s_1^{-1} = 4r$.
\begin{align*}
s_1 &= \frac{-1-r}4 \\
s_2 &= 4r \\
s_3 &= \frac{-1-r}4
\end{align*}
Hence $g(x) = \displaystyle \frac{1}{16}(x-s_1)(x-s_2)(x-s_3) = \frac{1}{16}(x^3-3x^2-4x+4)$.  The answer is $\mathbb{R}(-1)$, or $\boxed{-1}$. </think> <answer> -1 </answer>

